So I guess my sister is moving back home. She's fighting with her roommates, and today they called the cops on her for theft; clothes, cd's...basically everything she stole from me for the first 18 years I had to deal with her. The thing is, she claims they're all lying, and for the life of me I can't get myself to believe her. I have no sympathy for her. 

Anyway, there is a warrant out for her arrest and my parents are gonna end up having to bail her ass out of this mess as well. From the attorney fees to the fine for breaking rent, there goes the money that was supposed to go to my college education/housing. 

So, just to get straight to the point...there's a 90% chance I won't be going back to Tally in the fall. No words can explain how bad this hurts.

I fucking HATE her...

Alright first, I don't know who all reads this, but I know there are at least two people who know about my "situation" that really shouldn't know. And there are only a few ways they could have found out. I'm not making assumptions...all I know is they know, and I wasn't the one who told them. I realize they could have read this and that's fine too, but at least let me know you do. 

After tonight I'm debating weather I should have this fucking thing AT ALL. It's my journal...I will talk about personal things. Or would it be better if I just talk about the daisies and clouds and all that is wonderful and "normal" and leave it at that? 


<lj-cut text="Continued...For anyone who cares">I'm not offended that something was said. I'm offended that you hesitated to say it. The only reason there would be any hesitation is if you thought I would be uncomfortable because of my situation...or because YOU are uncomfortable with my situation. And I'm gonna go with the ladder becuase I have nothing to hide, and I am ashamed of nothing. If you have something to say...SAY IT. Spare me the awkward silences and the sideways glances. I can stomach a "10 inch dildo" joke just as well as the next person. Wether it be a cheap shot at my sexuality or not, I'd much rather be offended by a loud, obnoxious jerk than by a silent coward. Just say it! I'm a big girl, I can take it. Being me is hard enough. Dealing with the whispers just makes it worse. 

Make jokes, and say them loud...please! That way I can laugh with you. I AM NOT ASHAMED!!

I know people are uncomfortable with it, a lot of people are. Everyone is acting differnt around me...some can't even look me in the eye. And THAT hurts. Don't worry guys...it's not contagious. I promise, I don't smell, or act, or eat, or think, or breath, or bleed any differently than I did before. The only thing that has changed is...now you know something you didn't when you first met me.

If anyone is uncomfortable in my presence...you can tell me to stay home. If you can't eat at the same table with me without feeling as if you may "go there" then tell me to stay home. But I'm telling you now...it's ok to "go there".Just don't be a coward about it, because that is what makes it so offensive.</lj-cut>
